"title": "4357: salt",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4357",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A basic commodity, used for seasoning and preserving food in biblical times.</p>\n<h2>The importance of salt in the sacrificial system</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:13\">LEV 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:34-Exod30:35\">EXO 30:34–30:35</a> <em>The addition of salt to incense was probably to make it burn more easily and quickly</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:6-Ezra6:10\">EZR 6:6–6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:21-Ezra7:23\">EZR 7:21–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:22-Ezek43:24\">EZK 43:22–43:24</a></p>\n<h2>The covenant of salt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:17-Num18:19\">NUM 18:17–18:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:13\">LEV 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:4-2Chr13:5\">2CH 13:4–13:5</a></p>\n<h2>Believers as the salt of the earth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:13\">MAT 5:13</a></strong> <em>This teaching reflects the importance of salt as a preservative and seasoning.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:50\">MRK 9:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:34-Luke14:35\">LUK 14:34–14:35</a></p>\n<h2>Salt as a symbol of desolation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:9\">ZEP 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:23-Deut29:25\">DEU 29:23–29:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:5-Job39:6\">JOB 39:5–39:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:33-Ps107:34\">PSA 107:33–107:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:5-Jer17:8\">JER 17:5–17:8</a></p>\n<h2>Salt sown on arable land to render it worthless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:8-Jer48:9\">JER 48:8–48:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:42-Judg9:45\">JDG 9:42–9:45</a></p>\n<h2>Lot's wife turned into a pillar of salt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:23-Gen19:26\">GEN 19:23–19:26</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The Dead Sea an important source of salt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:11\">EZK 47:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Salt water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:9-Jas3:12\">JAS 3:9–3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:7-Ezek47:9\">EZK 47:7–47:9</a></p>\n<h2>Salt herbs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:4\">JOB 30:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Practical uses of salt</h2>\n<h3>Salt used as a seasoning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:6-Job6:7\">JOB 6:6–6:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Salt rubbed on newborn infants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:4\">EZK 16:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Symbolic use of salt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:19-2Kgs2:22\">2KI 2:19–2:22</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Figurative use of salt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:49\">MRK 9:49</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:14\">EZR 4:14</a> <em>The literal translation of the Hebrew phrase used here is “... we eat the salt of the palace ...”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:6\">COL 4:6</a></p>\n<h2>Salt in place-names</h2>\n<h3>The Dead Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh12:3\">JOS 12:3</a></strong> <em>The Dead Sea was known as “the Salt Sea” or “the Sea of the Arabah” in biblical times.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:3\">GEN 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:3-Num34:4\">NUM 34:3–34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:10-Num34:12\">NUM 34:10–34:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:16-Deut3:17\">DEU 3:16–3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:15-Josh3:16\">JOS 3:15–3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:2-Josh15:3\">JOS 15:2–15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:5-Josh15:6\">JOS 15:5–15:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:19\">JOS 18:19</a></p>\n<h3>The Valley of Salt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:13\">2SA 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:7\">2KI 14:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:11\">2CH 25:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:12\">1CH 18:12</a></p>\n<h3>The City of Salt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:62\">JOS 15:62</a></strong></p>",
